fields.title: Hyundai Complimentary Maintenance
fields.description:
HMA will announce effective February 1, 2020, that any MY 2020 vehicle sold (with certain exceptions) will come with 3-Yr Complimentary Maintenance.  The Hyundai Complimentary Maintenance service includes oil, oil filter, and tire rotation services at recommended mileages.  There will be two service schedules – Non-Turbo and Turbo engines.  Non-Turbo will be 7500mi intervals and Turbo will be 6000mi intervals. _x000D_
There will be guardrails on both side of the intervals for eligibility.  1000 miles before mileage interval and 1000 miles after.  Outside of the guardrails, the service may be customer paid._x000D_
Hyundai Capital Insurance (HCI) will develop an API for all parties to call to return back eligibility for complimentary service and the balance of services remaining.  Each application requiring the information will call HCI’s API to get this information.  _x000D_
Current systems identified as being impacted are the following (this list may change and the requirements become more clear:_x000D_
- AS/400 Warranty_x000D_
- WebDCS_x000D_
- Siebel CRM_x000D_
- CVA_x000D_
- EDW_x000D_
- MyHyundai Web and Mobile App_x000D_
- Epsilon Owner Marketing_x000D_
- Service Lane Technology (SLT)

fields.title: HMA Dealer Package Mgmt System Replacement
fields.description:
HMA and GMA market representation requires a web based system to manage dealership organizational changes and information collection.  _x000D_
The system needs to facilitate the request, collection, storing and distribution of information, documents and agreements.  The system also requires a workflow to manage the data collection, review and approval processes to ensure they are completed in a certain timeline and satisfy oversight requirements.  _x000D_
_x000D_
Dealer organizational change processes have been classified into “Packages” to determine information collection and review/approval requirements. _x000D_
_x000D_
The system will request dealers to provide information, documents, and complete agreements in order to satisfy the package requirements within a specified timeline.  Dealer provided information is reviewed and approved by regional and national users in dealer development, legal and sales.  _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
Issues:_x000D_
•	Current system lacks the ability for business teams to manage changes to workflows and participants  _x000D_
•	Limited automation capability.  _x000D_
o	Support information must be manually collected from external systems and input into DPMS adding significant time and creates opportunities for errors/omissions._x000D_
o	Unable to merge data into Agreements _x000D_
•	Esignature integration is not currently available _x000D_
•	Limited windows to update documentation and agreements.  Updates must be timed to not impact packages that are in progress.  _x000D_
•	Inconsistency in text formatting areas slows data analysis. _x000D_
•	Business users cannot run reports for analysis_x000D_
•	Unable to track dealer contacts or information in a single location_x000D_
•	Unable to share documentation among departments and users within system

At an industry level, the majority of OEMs/Dealers use companies such as Darwin Online or Dealer Socket to transact prepaid maintenance sales and other aftersale products.
